Class RestConfigFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ge.predix.solsvc.restclient.config.RestConfigFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.beans.factory.Aware, org.springframework.context.ApplicationContextAware

    @Component
public class RestConfigFactory
extends Object
implements org.springframework.context.ApplicationContextAware
    If you are not using Environment variables (or properties), you can programatically create a Config using this Factory class. This will use the DefaultConfig as a baseline. This is helpful when your microservice is handling multiple user or clients or endpoints

      • clientCredentials

        public static IOauthRestConfig clientCredentials(String oauthIssuerId,
                                                 String oauthClientIdColonSecret,
                                                 boolean oauthClientIdEncode)
        Use this to generate a client token with grant_type=client_credentials
        Parameters:
        oauthIssuerId - - Issuer ID URL of the UAA
        oauthClientIdColonSecret - - clientId:secret separated by a colon
        oauthClientIdEncode - - whether the SDK should base64 encode the clientId:secret, default is true. true means it is clear-text. false is what you should do in order to not display the secret in clear-text.
        Returns:
        -

      • passwordGrant

        public static IOauthRestConfig passwordGrant(String oauthIssuerId,
                                             String oauthClientIdColonSecret,
                                             boolean oauthClientIdEncode,
                                             String oauthUserName,
                                             String oauthUserPassword,
                                             boolean oauthEncodeUserPassword)
        Use this to generate a client token with grant_type=password
        Parameters:
        oauthIssuerId - - Issuer ID URL of the UAA
        oauthClientIdColonSecret - - clientId:secret separated by a colon
        oauthClientIdEncode - - whether the clientId:secret is base 64 encoded when passed in, default is true
        oauthUserName - - the username to generate a token for. As set up in UAA or the UAA Federated IDP.
        oauthUserPassword - - the password of the user
        oauthEncodeUserPassword - - whether to base64 encode the password, default is true
        Returns:
        -
